Use the standard library
This is how to int_to_mini_roman of number:
   Remember that n is number
   Remember that result is ""
   Do this quotient of n and 100 times:
      Add result to "c"
   End do
   Remember that n is remainder of n and 100
   When n is at least 90, then:
      Add result to "xc"
      Remember that n is diff of n and 90
   But, if not:
      When n is at least 50, then:
         Add result to "l"
         Remember that n is diff of n and 50
      End when
      When n is at least 40, then:
         Add result to "xl"
         Remember that n is diff of n and 40
      End when
      Do this quotient of n and 10 times:
         Add result to "x"
      End do
      Remember that n is remainder of n and 10
   End when
   When n is 9, then:
      Add result to "ix"
      Remember that n is 0
   But, if not:
      When n is at least 5, then:
         Add result to "v"
         Remember that n is diff of n and 5
      End when
      When n is 4, then:
         Add result to "iv"
         Remember that n is 0
      But, if not:
         Do this n times:
            Add result to "i"
         End do
      End when
   End when
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> int_to_mini_roman of 19
"xix"
>>> toarray of (int_to_mini_roman of 19)
[120, 105, 120]
>>> int_to_mini_roman of 152
"clii"